<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000922/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """In accordance with the "Normativa de Evaluación del Aprendizaje de la Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, 26/05/2022", all the students will be assessed using the same evaluation method, which should be progressive by default. Moreover, students who do not pass the subject through the progressive evaluation will be given the opportunity to be additionally evaluated through the global assessment method. The evaluation process aims to verify if the students have acquired all the competences and learning outcomes of the subject. Thus, the global assessment method will be carried out using the same evaluation criteria and techniques employed in the progressive evaluation method.
Evaluation activities that assess learning outcomes that cannot be recovered outside the teaching period are mandatory. These activities are clearly described and justified in this Learning Guide.
The evaluation of this subject involves:
PROGRESSIVE EVALUATION (100 %)
The progressive evaluation is based on the submission of reports corresponding to the various homework assignments and design exercises related to the different topics of the subject. The final grade will be calculated as the weighted average of the scores obtained in all homework tasks plus the final design project.
GLOBAL EVALUATION (100 %)
For the students who require the global assessment, the evaluation is based on the submission of all proposed homework assignments and the final design project, along with a question-and-answer session about their content. This activity will take place during the exam period on the official exam date established by the Junta de Escuela.
EXTRAORDINARY ASSESSMENT (100 %)
The extraordinary evaluation will follow the global evaluation method described above."""@es .

